# Environment setup instructions

## Required Environment Variables

Set these in your Cloudflare Workers dashboard under Settings > Environment Variables:

### Required Variables
# Get from @BotFather on Telegram - NEVER commit real values
TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=your_telegram_bot_token_here

# Get from Google AI Studio - NEVER commit real values  
GEMINI_API_KEY=your_gemini_api_key_here

# Any random string for webhook security - NEVER commit real values
WEBHOOK_SECRET=your_webhook_secret_here

### KV Namespace
# Create a KV namespace called "LEITNER_DB" and update the IDs in wrangler.toml

## Setup Steps

1. Create Telegram bot with @BotFather
2. Get Google Gemini API key from https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey
3. Create Cloudflare KV namespace
4. Set environment variables in Cloudflare Workers dashboard
5. Deploy via GitHub Actions

## Security Notes
- NEVER commit .env files with real API keys
- Use GitHub Secrets for CI/CD deployment
- Rotate API keys regularly
- Use different keys for staging/production

Detailed instructions are in README.md
